social_posts.post_text:
I said goodbye to my hero this morning - My Dad. 

You showed me how to be a good dad, you showed me how to be a good husband, you showed me how to be a servant of others but most importantly you showed me your love. You introduced me to the cowboy life, bull riding, rodeo, hunting but more importantly you introduced me to Jesus. 

If I can make a fraction of the impact you had on others then I’ll count it a success. You were amazing! 

I’ll miss you every day for the rest of my life but this isn’t goodbye forever, I’ll see you when I get there! 🤠♥️

Merry Christmas from our family to yours. 🙏🏼 
Luke 2:11

Being Thankful is the secret sauce to keeping your attitude in check. 

We all have problems so don’t feel like the Lone Ranger and it would be easy for us to sit around and complain about them. That won’t do you any good. 

Focus on the important things that you are thankful for and if you do this consistently, you’ll see a change in your attitude. 🙏🏼🤠

What a special evening for our family. The Western Sports Foundation honored Stran Smith the the very first Ted Wiese Memorial Award. This award is so special to us as a family and embodies individuals in the rodeo and western community that truly have a servants heart, that lead and mentor behind the scenes and hold the values of faith and family without question. Stran couldn’t have been a more perfect choice to be the first recipient of this award. Dad would have been proud.
